'DtoToEntity' adlı üye örnek verilerine erişmiyor ve statik olarak işaretlenebilir

CA1822.fullDescription: Örnek verilerine erişmeyen veya örnek yöntemlerini çağırmayan üyeler statik olarak işaretlenebilir. Yöntemleri statik olarak işaretledikten sonra, derleyici bu üyelere yönelik sanal olmayan çağrı konumlarını gösterir. Bu, performans açısından duyarlı kod için önemli ölçüde performans kazanımı sağlar.

CA1860.fullDescription: 'Enumerable.Any()' metodunu çağırmak yerine hangisi mevcutsa 'IsEmpty', 'Count' veya 'Length' özelliklerinden birini kullanmayı tercih edin. Amaç daha kolay anlaşılır ve 'Enumerable.Any()' genişletme metoduna göre daha yüksek performans sunar.

CS8613.shortDescription: Dönüş türündeki başvuru türlerinin boş değer atanabilirliği, örtük olarak uygulanan üye ile eşleşmiyor.

CS8618.shortDescription: Null atanamaz alan, oluşturucudan çıkış yaparken null olmayan bir değer içermelidir. 'Gerekli' değiştiricisini ekleyin veya null atanabilir olarak bildirmeyi göz önünde bulundurun.

S108.shortDescription: Nested blocks of code should not be left empty
S108.fullDescription: An empty code block is confusing. It will require some effort from maintainers to determine if it is intentional or indicates the implementation is incomplete.

S1118.shortDescription: Utility classes should not have public constructors
S1118.fullDescription: Whenever there are portions of code that are duplicated and do not depend on the state of their container class, they can be centralized inside a "utility class". A utility class is a class that only has static members, hence it should not be instantiated.

S112.shortDescription: General or reserved exceptions should never be thrown
S112.fullDescription: This rule raises an issue when a general or reserved exception is thrown.

S1192.shortDescription: String literals should not be duplicated
S1192.fullDescription: Duplicated string literals make the process of refactoring complex and error-prone, as any change would need to be propagated on all occurrences.

S125.shortDescription: Sections of code should not be commented out
S125.fullDescription: Commented-out code distracts the focus from the actual executed code. It creates a noise that increases maintenance code. And because it is never executed, it quickly becomes out of date and invalid.

S1481.shortDescription: Unused local variables should be removed
S1481.fullDescription: An unused local variable is a variable that has been declared but is not used anywhere in the block of code where it is defined. It is dead code, contributing to unnecessary complexity and leading to confusion when reading the code. Therefore, it should be removed from your code to maintain clarity and efficiency.

S2486.shortDescription: Generic exceptions should not be ignored
S2486.fullDescription: When exceptions occur, it is usually a bad idea to simply ignore them. Instead, it is better to handle them properly, or at least to log them.

S2737.shortDescription: "catch" clauses should do more than rethrow
S2737.fullDescription: A catch clause that only rethrows the caught exception has the same effect as omitting the catch altogether and letting it bubble up automatically.

S4487.fullDescription: Private fields which are written but never read are a case of "dead store". Changing the value of such a field is useless and most probably indicates an error in the code.

S5122.shortDescription: Having a permissive Cross-Origin Resource Sharing policy is security-sensitive
S5122.fullDescription: Having a permissive Cross-Origin Resource Sharing policy is security-sensitive. It has led in the past to the following vulnerabilities:

S6444.shortDescription: Not specifying a timeout for regular expressions is security-sensitive
S6444.fullDescription: Not specifying a timeout for regular expressions can lead to a Denial-of-Service attack. Pass a timeout when using System.Text.RegularExpressions to process untrusted input because a malicious user might craft a value for which the evaluation lasts excessively long.

S6961.shortDescription: API Controllers should derive from ControllerBase instead of Controller
S6961.fullDescription: In ASP.NET Core, controllers usually inherit either from ControllerBase or Controller. If a controller does not use any View-specific functionality, it is recommended to inherit from ControllerBase.

S6964.shortDescription: Value type property used as input in a controller action should be nullable, required or annotated with the JsonRequiredAttribute to avoid under-posting.
S6964.fullDescription: "Under-posting" refers to a situation where a client sends less data than expected to the server during an HTTP request, for example when the client omits some properties from the request body that the server expects to receive.
